================================================================================
Third-party data attribution
================================================================================

The demo storefront ("Nimbus") ships a committed, signed product catalog bundle
at `backend/examples/catalog/` (720 products, balanced across 12 categories,
60 each). That catalog is a small curated subset derived from:

    Amazon Reviews 2023 (item metadata)
    Authors: Yupeng Hou, Jiacheng Li, Zhankui He, An Yan, Xiusi Chen,
             Julian McAuley (McAuley Lab, UC San Diego)
    Source:  https://amazon-reviews-2023.github.io/
             (Hugging Face: McAuley-Lab/Amazon-Reviews-2023)
    Cite:    Hou et al., "Bridging Language and Items for Retrieval and
             Recommendation," 2024 (arXiv:2403.03952).
    Use:     released for academic / research use.

The committed bundle was produced by curating a balanced subset from the source
metadata (`backend/scripts/curate_demo_catalog.py` -> `backend/examples/source/
catalog.csv`), then `edgereco build-catalog` -> `edgereco index` ->
`edgereco bundle`. You can regenerate it with the same commands (see README).

